records.addlTxt: 11:43 a.m.  Defendant Chandra Mae Pickett in court with attorney T Gregory Amann.  William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Thorie - amended information, plead guilty to amended charge. S/W - 1 year, expungement if successfully completed, no restitution.  Amann agrees.  Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.    Constitutional rights explained to defendant.    Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights.    DEF PLEADS GUILTY to Count 1 in the Amended Information.    Facts are correct in the Amended Information.    COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.    The court finds the defendant guilty and adjudicates defendant guilty of Count 1 of the Amended Information.  Court orders S/W - 1 year probation, conditions to be set by agent.  Court costs in the amount of $443.00 which  includes DNA surcharge.  Expungement upon successful completion of probation.  Appeal rights given.

11:43 a.m.  Defendant Chandra Mae Pickett in court with attorney T Gregory Amann.  William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def

11:11 a.m.  Defendant Marshall Ellery James D Grotto in court with attorney Daniel James Chapman.  William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Chandra Mae Pickett in court with attorney T Gregory Amann for Case 2015CF110 .  Preliminary hearing to be held together for 15CF108 and 15CF110.  Thorie calls Officer Thomas Koen.  Koen is sworn and takes the stand.  Thorie examines Officer Koen.  Koen identifies defendants Marshall Grotto and Chandra Pickett.  Chapman x-ex Koen.  Amann x-ex Koen. Sgt Eric Michels is swn, ex by Thorie. ID's Chandra Pickett and Marshall Grotto. Atty Chapman x ex Sgt Michels. Atty Amann x ex Sgt Michels.  Atty Chapman gives argument; no bind over. Atty Amann gives argument and requests dismissal. Atty Thorie gives argument.  Court: entry to the building is clear; private property. finds the defendants probably commited a felony and binds over for trial.  Atty Chapman addresses consent issue and hearsay. Atty Thorie responds.

Thorie files information; Defendants have a copy. Court reads charges and maximum penalties on both cases. Both defendants waiver further reading. Marshall Grotto pleas not guilty to charges. Chandra Pickett pleas not guilty. Court receives not guilty pleas. Attorney's to get new hearing dates.
Def waives her right to have her preliminary hearing within 20 days.
